{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-chapter-level-2-chapter-level-2-tsx","path":"/topics/benign-paroxysmal-positional-vertigo/how-this-topic-was-developed/evidence-exclusion-criteria/","result":{"pageContext":{"chapter":{"id":"e9b89bf6-5c75-57fa-8809-56cabe90b3f8","slug":"evidence-exclusion-criteria","fullItemName":"Evidence exclusion criteria","depth":2,"htmlHeader":"<!-- begin field 4eccfe3b-517f-4c8c-8b69-a7f2018881dd --><h2>Evidence exclusion criteria</h2><!-- end field 4eccfe3b-517f-4c8c-8b69-a7f2018881dd -->","summary":null,"htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item b5475ff3-2719-44b3-832e-a7f20187a3cf --><!-- begin field a4779e39-9e56-4fec-aba4-a7f2018881dd --><h2>Our policy</h2><!-- end field a4779e39-9e56-4fec-aba4-a7f2018881dd --><!-- begin field 9aca8362-480a-418b-858e-a7f2018881dd --><p>Scoping a literature search, and reviewing the evidence for CKS is a methodical and systematic process that is carried out by the lead clinical author for each topic. Relevant evidence is gathered in order that the clinical author can make fully informed decisions and recommendations. It is important to note that some evidence may be excluded for a variety of reasons. These reasons may be applied across all CKS topics or may be specific to a given topic.</p><p>Studies identified during literature searches are reviewed to identify the most appropriate information to author a CKS topic, ensuring any recommendations are based on the best evidence. We use the principles of the GRADE and PICOT approaches to assess the quality of published research. We use the principles of AGREE II to assess the quality of published guidelines.</p><!-- end field 9aca8362-480a-418b-858e-a7f2018881dd --><!-- begin field 555eb160-79a3-4b24-8303-a7f2018881dd --><h2>Standard exclusions for scoping literature:</h2><!-- end field 555eb160-79a3-4b24-8303-a7f2018881dd --><!-- begin field 03a2578c-5066-4ee6-9d97-a7f2018881dd --><ul><li>Animal studies</li><li>Original research is not written in English</li></ul><!-- end field 03a2578c-5066-4ee6-9d97-a7f2018881dd --><!-- begin field ed595f2a-9571-44e0-ab89-a7f2018881dd --><h2>Possible exclusions for reviewed literature:</h2><!-- end field ed595f2a-9571-44e0-ab89-a7f2018881dd --><!-- begin field b19411e0-44c6-4592-9478-a7f2018881dd --><ul><li>Sample size too small or study underpowered</li><li>Bias evident or promotional literature</li><li>Population not relevant</li><li>Intervention/treatment not relevant</li><li>Outcomes not relevant</li><li>Outcomes have no clear evidence of clinical effectiveness</li><li>Setting not relevant</li><li>Not relevant to UK</li><li>Incorrect study type</li><li>Review article</li><li>Duplicate reference</li></ul><!-- end field b19411e0-44c6-4592-9478-a7f2018881dd --><!-- end item b5475ff3-2719-44b3-832e-a7f20187a3cf -->","topic":{"id":"eea62555-eafd-5d57-89f9-cf642a03c23e","topicId":"2d4ab605-73d9-4d0d-81b2-63f813bffbf4","topicName":"Benign paroxysmal positional vertigo","slug":"benign-paroxysmal-positional-vertigo","lastRevised":"Last revised in October 2017","chapters":[{"id":"55de1e3b-a340-57ae-b6bd-5a23274137d9","fullItemName":"Summary","slug":"summary","subChapters":[]},{"id":"618c59d0-aae9-5d66-af1f-04a721bdc613","fullItemName":"Have I got the right topic?","slug":"have-i-got-the-right-topic","subChapters":[]},{"id":"c4385463-008f-5f2e-8997-4b2b570eb03f","fullItemName":"How up-to-date is this topic?","slug":"how-up-to-date-is-this-topic","subChapters":[{"id":"e1854357-1131-5121-8afa-0dbf6b8c0da3","slug":"changes","fullItemName":"Changes"},{"id":"afa34ca4-0365-55b8-80ef-a3e67e18d956","slug":"update","fullItemName":"Update"}]},{"id":"3f12f1a7-1a22-5bd6-a3d7-f3170c70e39e","fullItemName":"Goals and outcome measures","slug":"goals-outcome-measures","subChapters":[{"id":"e93cb05b-35aa-57c1-83ad-c9acb5b58fd7","slug":"goals","fullItemName":"Goals"},{"id":"5bd99271-7240-5a7f-ab8b-9ce87f39759a","slug":"outcome-measures","fullItemName":"Outcome measures"},{"id":"99de36b6-0f8f-5c4c-ad7